description.narrative: An estimated 544,060 (of 742,043) children under five were treated diarrhoea with oral rehydration solution (ORS with zinc) by community development and health agents (ADECOS). All 18 provinces developed their costed prevention of mother to child HIV transmission (PMTCT) expansion plans. More than 4.5 million children received mono-valent type 2 oral polio vaccine in response supplementary vaccination activities to polio-vaccine derived (cVDPVD2) outbreaks. | Status:Partially Met | As-of Date:18/12/2019
